Detailed Description

Packet used when getting the nodes on a map edge which also exist on the supplied level.

After the normal RequestPacket header the packet contains (X is REQUEST_HEADER_SIZE):
PosSizeComment
X 4 bytes Level to check
X + 4 4 bytes User defined data. Should be copied to the reply.
X + 8 4 bytes Vehicle to check for allowance

Creates a new EdgeNodesRequestPacket for the specified mapID and level.

Also implies that the RouteModule should try to avoid nodes that cannot be used by the supplied vehicle.

Parameters:
packetID The packetID of the packet.
requestID The requestID of the packet.
mapID The map to check.
level The absolute level where the nodes must exist.
dests The destinations (if any).
vehicles The vi
userDef User defined data. Should be copied to the reply by the module.
